< Text>
Frozen Fruit Co remains one of my favorite dessert spots in LA. It still amazes me how creamy their chocolate "ice cream" is while still being vegan! I'm glad that they're still open during covid (delivery & takeout). It's a cozy shop so only one party is allowed at a time and you need to wear a mask.

No samples since it's covid but all the flavors are good (and that's not hyperbole). Nevertheless chocolate is, and forever will be, my favorite. There's the slightest hint of coconut but it's smooth and melts perfectly in your mouth. Since it's dairy-free, it doesn't feel as heavy as regular ice cream would but still tastes just as decadent. The passion fruit sorbet also perfectly balances a slight tartness with natural sweetness from the fruit. There's no ice participles like there would be from a lesser quality sorbet but it's still refreshingly cool. Definitely make a stop here!< /Text>

<rate>5</rate>< Text>
Small plant-based dessert shop on Montana Ave. This is one of my favorite spots to come to for dessert. The people working there are always very affable and helpful. There‚Äôs metered street parking or you can try your luck on the neighborhood and walk. I like coming here after dinner at Fathers Office and I frequently take out of town guests here. You can try samples of the flavors, and there‚Äôs usually a couple of seasonal flavors to try. This most recent visit I tried the banana pumpkin spice which tasted like autumn. The texture was really creamy and you wouldn‚Äôt be able to guess that it‚Äôs vegan. However my all time favorite is the chocolate. There is a strong underlying taste of coconut so if you don‚Äôt like coconut, it may not be for you. However I really like how smooth and creamy it is, and it‚Äôs not as heavy as regular ice cream. You can customize your small or large cup with toppings (50 cents each, $1 for marshmallows) and there are some indoor seats where you can people watch. There‚Äôs also some benches and chairs right outside by the fountain. The coffee flavor I had with the chocolate was a nice complement and you can taste the freshness. Overall, love this place for the lovely staff, tasty dessert, and cute atmosphere.</Text>

<rating>5<//rating>< Text>
On a Saturday shopping trip, we ran across, parked on Ventura Boulevard,  a bright pink truck, that dispensed plant-based ice cream.

The friendly, knowledgeable, driver/server, Bobby, offered free samples of their house-made, three ingredient, gluten and soy free, vegan, coconut milk "ice cream."

I sampled about a half dozen flavors and ordered a scoop of the Salted Chocolate.  It was served in a cup, at the perfect temperature, gently firm, unbelievably smooth and delicious. My partner loved her creamy, decadent Chocolate scoop. Servings are large. Cones are not offered.

Fresh fruit, natural sugars, and coconut milk are used in their frozen wonders. And it shows. Bobby's teaspoon size samples are wonderful. They tasted of their named fruit with the underlying flavor of coconut - fresh and delightful. However, the Strawberry Sorbet, made without coconut, contained ice crystals.

If you get lucky and find the pink truck, do yourself a favor and enjoy.</Text>

I love this place! Really yummy vegan ice cream, and they keep it super simple with no more than 5 ingredients to make their ice cream! <review>What a unique concept for a frozen, sweet and healthy treat. I was craving just that while out on Montana running errands and Frozen Fruit Co delivered!

The pineapple and passion fruit was perfectly crafted and I love the texture. The portion was generous and you can add toppings for .50 cents each. I took mine straight up and it was still perfect.

The only drawback was not knowing more of how it was made and what else was in it. I asked, but the response was somewhat vague.

Overall, a tasty treat, cute branding, plenty of seating and a lovely fountain just outside that you can sit by. For a brief taste of Hawaii, I recommend coming in for a treat that won't leave you with a sugar hangover.

Pro Tips:
- Check in with Yelp to receive a 10% discount<//review><username>Ashley Sundquist</username>< Resp>

< review>
Pros- the staff was extremely nice, and my massage therapist spent a lot of time working some really sore spots on me that were really problematic. I enjoyed the massage and did feel a bit better when I left. She kindly waited outside to offer me water when I left. I know this is common, but it was still a personal touch I enjoy.

Cons- there were quite a few spots during my massage when my massage therapist would grind into a spot that was less centered on the muscles than on the ends of them if that makes any sense. She didn't work those spots for an extended amount of time so it wasn't problematic, but it wasn't where I'd expect to be massaged by a professional.
Finally, as I was paying, I asked the receptionist to add in a 20% tip to my bill. My total before adding a tip was $65. She added a $21 tip to my bill. Before I left, I asked where she got that total from and she pointed to a piece of paper on the counter that appeared to have tip rates (I didn't bother to read it). I won't begrudge them a few extra dollars, but if that piece of paper says $21 dollars is 20% of a $65 bill, the person who came up with those totals should be fired, and anyone who thinks that math is correct needs to look a little closer. I won't be returning.< /review>

< user>
106015435310306810969<//user>
<name>Valencia</name><time>1618264909511<//time><Rate>5<//Rate>< Review>
There is no place in Visalia to get better fried rice. One of these days I will find out your secrets Lao Noodle House!! One thing I love about this establishment is their sizes. They have a variety of sizes for every dish, from small to either extra-large or extra-extra-large (I can't quite remember)
Let me tell you, an extra-large fried rice will last you a couple days, and it's just as good reheated! You can also get amazing soup or pad Thai here, depending on whatever your craving. Don't forget to add on a Thai iced tea and some chicken and rice to make the perfect meal.
The staff is so friendly and interactive- the owner and his son are really fun to chat with!
Keep in mind they only accept cash payment. As of right now, it's only take-out due to COVID, so they'll remind you on the phone that it's cash only. Honestly not a big deal for me personally but it is a good thing to remember.
For the three years I've lived in the area, Lao Noodle House has been a regular visit for me, and that's not going to change any time soon!< /Review>

< review>
They have forever lost my business. I bought my wife a Lady's Smith 357 at the Costa Mesa gun show and of course it's busy and we were passed off several times to various people until we finally got all the paperwork done. I'd say I took about an hour from start to finish. Now the wait is on. The reason for the purchase was we were planning a range day trip of about eight friends up to some property in Campo and we were really excited to try out this new pistol. We had plenty of time to get the gun since we cod pick it up after the ten day hold. We get it Tuesday and we can get a new holster and a few other things so she can be comfortable with her new gun. Ten days comes and goes so we jump in the car and drive up to the Mira Mar store but when we get there they can't find the gun. Actually they can't even find the paperwork let alone the almost $800 gun. So about 40 minutes later we get the "I'll call you tomorrow" line. Well tomorrow comes and goes and still nothing. I waited another day and still got nothing. I call back and nobody knows what going on with the missing gun and paperwork. Well of course I'm not real happy with the lack of customer service and so I start calling the other branches to try and get ahold of a manage or regional manager that can get me some answers. No one can help so I call the San Diego branch again and got some really nice guy that seemed to care and he promised me that someone would call me right away. That was the best service I received from this company. About five minutes later I got some guy with an attitude and very unapologetic call me and say he was the general manager. He said they were shorthanded and they didn't know were the gun was because it never got unloaded from the Costa Mesa gun show. He said all the paperwork was fine and the background check was good but the gun was sent to the Las Vegas Shot show. How does this happen? Yeah, just "short handed", not sorry? Not what I wanted to hear. I get a call back from the one guy that was helpful and asked if I wanted to cancel the transaction but I'd eat the almost $40 that goes to the state so I said no. He told me he would have the gun Monday and I'd get a call when it came in. Of course we didn't get to take it to range day so there's that, and wouldn't you know it, no call on Monday. I finally called on Tuesday and had to explain everything again to the guy on the phone and he said "bummer". Well yeah this has been a major bummer. My wife picked up the gun on Thursday since she was in the area and they offered her a 10% discount on ammo when she was there. That's not how you fix this colossal screw up on your part. I was warned by several of my friends that have had their own bad experiences with ammo bros but I made the mistake of not listening. Listen to this, I will never use ammo bros again. One star for the guy that helped, thanks dude<//review>

<rating>5<//rating><review>Finally checking this place out! Always past the food truck and knew this was close by. Finally made it to the location! Right by the old farrell's ice cream parlor in small Shopping plaza, plenty of parking!

Limited Dining is allow, takeout, and delivery are other options as well. Large selection of tacos starting at $2.97, burritos, mulitas, Tortas, quesadilla, sopes, and various sides.

Went with lengua (it's tough to find), cabeza, and tripas (she offer to fried it and said it taste better as such). Pal went with pollo and al pastor and a side of rice. They ask if we wanted cilantro and onions on our tacos and we opted  for them.

2 corn tortillas Street taco style with our choice but was missing cilantro and onion but came with red and green salsa and lime wedges.

Meat was very tender. Fried tripas was crunchy and did not taste heavy nor was it overly greasy. Cabeza and lengua was soft, easy to chew, melt in your mouth.

If your looking for alcohol, they do not serve any here.

Service was friendly and great to support another local business! Definitely will return!<//review><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNMWhbdxVi6NX3rFI-2MyfCAqEE_aZZ97Y2AgJC=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMdAQ9uKCr1_TKMIyrKDx24zOP8oY1h0elG6PdY=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNdYvS7AJ5taWKtOZdQNYgZHJRIFDs9psNada1X=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMQRuUOIp6SKAmQHeKb48BPoacnj50Mh5H_Jine=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNYP9XGVxXKVXlzVu3mDvZBwR0jbSCwT6ey3D40=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOWqEtaRgpkJz6Wbpgle99RQRDWUVSJEdH3-WyT=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipORawK_kDT78TwYZMntkF8dYaFwSGbtdct7nqPc=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNuHwFboHvGU6hc--7mhHsOCxHkkno_NfKDoOBq=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNy0XdHg9Eg0yO_ZXzGL6Ya4LgxRs5oQsTZz4qL=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMxaXKBTrE3nsOJ2cuc_yjabi28ATtt1P-DOXb7=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNXMWJShHT0JeYOrBDffrUZ79Oefa06ZIsGryOw=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOVWq0i06UW8AzWrca6fpL850GUCGWWHYWcli_E=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPsHZoaBqMm340V_RgvWXsSjBZj--NSe-aLVdSA=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMu2HelHpRsMZv-YXi9-GkqEL-ej4g4J4oS678L=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPY0wmUvmtlp0VXw2tFZmpY6lk072_-VV9qfaNO=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pictures><Response>None</Response>< GmapID>

3<//rate>
<Review>I'm always up for a new place especially if the focus is on the food. This makes it convenient if the place is small because the food can be taken out and enjoyed without losing the feel of the place.
That is important here because it is smaller and could be crowded easily.

The variety is small but that is not necessarily a negative.  That means they combine what they have without going outside the core which in this case  is the meats.

The meats are well prepared,  and do not need a lot of sauces or additions to make them satisfying. There is a area for sauces that can help but not necessary with the basic taco or burrito.

The main drawback here is the beans, I am kinda judgy about the refried beans and here they dont cut it. Bland and just filler. The other thing is the staff did not seems enthused to be there. So why should I be?

So, grab some tacos,  skip the beans and take it to go.

As always I say, try different things here for yourself, they have lengua, cabeza  and other meats to try, and judge for yourself.</Review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN8PrRHDLtMEzafApmbG7i1di21G6TXjeXxy4cT=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNk125Vz8n2V-Z1_ZXP9eukGmMlTHHaPpdzYiLy=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMscmTtFd4YwfeX-lMInmdtyD5loOX92uYRkxra=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMEdy2tBDNgsKm-z3NLxMcmruJ0gesqJmdIPS-I=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMilBndB3oxCsAPq77KiobAJXcbODVcLC9V2qci=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOjpadb9UgdBtftjXPWn5OrPTi0v7uTEA2CB8VH=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pictures>< resp>

Or we have to place an order and drive to pick it up...which defeats the purpose of using and paying for a delivery. Hopefully we get the credit for the already overpriced food that we did not get to eat.<//review>

I‚Äôve tried about half of the ‚Äúclassic‚Äù flavors, but I‚Äôm slowly getting there. The bars are great for physically active individuals that find themselves on the go often (I wouldn‚Äôt recommend these for your average soccer mom or dad as the bars are calorie dense and filled with sugar). Opening the package for this bar I detected a faint banana aroma. The bar is a brown color with a fair amount of peanuts and dark chocolate chips visible. There is also a gleam to the bar and I noticed it‚Äôs a little stickier than its contemporaries. Unlike most granola bars, this bar is short and thick. Like all the other CLIF Bars I‚Äôve tried this one is chewy, dense, and moist in the mouth (kind of like a good brownie). Along with the chew there is a slight crunch from the peanuts. This proved to be the perfect CLIF Bar for me as I love bananas, peanut butter, and chocolate. My followers know I don‚Äôt really dig dark chocolate, but the dark chocolate taste is not too apparent in my opinion. If dark chocolate wasn‚Äôt in the name I probably would assume it was my preferred milk chocolate. The banana flavor is really what sells it for me though as it is superb. Not only is it my favorite classic bar flavor, but it‚Äôs Doughboy approved. @clifbar
My favorite CLIF bars:
1. Peanut Butter Banana with Dark Chocolate
2. White Chocolate Macadamia
3. Chocolate Chip Peanut Crunch tied with Peanut Butter& Honey
4. Chocolate Brownie

<UserId.>100426505945993106445</UserId.><name>Alissa Canto< /name>< date>
1552454966736< /date>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< Review>
This is about the customer service I received online, and I don't know where to put this! Last month I got some Cliff bars from the Rexburg Mobile Food Pantry and I am pretty much Celiac and super sensitive to gluten. Many of the bars I've had from their brand I'm fine with (except the oatmeal raisin), and usually the products that say 'may contain wheat' aren't that bad and I don't have a reaction. But there was one type of energy bar that actually HAD wheat in it (Malt has wheat!) and I had a terrible allergy reaction that lasted two days and I could barely do anything. I talked to customer service about how the product was mislabeled and they offered me bars from their gluten free selection. They mailed me my two favorite types of Luna Bars -- the Lemon bar and the Peppermint. I felt so loved and cared for and appreciated!! I've been buying their bars since 2012 and I plan on being a life-long customer. This really made my day when I received my favorites!</Review>

<name>Matteo Capanna</name>< text>
I needed some new tires as my 215/50R17 MXM4 Michelin tires had failed to hold air at 3/32.  I would describe the tread as flaky with moderately cracked side wall to boot after nearly 4 years of use.  Let's just say they didn't make the 55,000 mark but I did a little more dirt and gravel driving than most people expose their tires to.
Knowing that I would be doing less rural and more highway driving I want something quite, comfortable, with some honest longevity.
Having purchased many tires of different brand and quality, I put Justin at ATD through the paces finding just the right tire for my needs.  I told him what I wanted, what I didn't, and what I currently was looking at.  After narrowing down the field, we battered around impression of a few tires.  Not only was the service and price excellent, we found a solution that could be installed the same day. I appreciate them getting me out the door to pick up my kids on time from school.  Thank you so much for the great tire buying experience!
So you're probably wondering what tires I chose?  Yokohama Avid Ascend GT.  It's only been a trip to Pismo for the weekend, a little rural driving in Templeton, and a couple days of usual driving in Clovis and Fresno.  My impressions: The Yokohama hands down better traction the the Michelin ever had, I'm truly impressed with the grip on clean flat roads, sandy roads, and oddly shape dips on hilly roads.
Next they are slightly noisier than than the MXM4s, but you can only tell that with the radio off, so not a deal breaker.
Both tires are 95V rated and the handling is similar.  Putting the tires through the paces is not wise when this new, but it handled all the curvy roads in a comfortably agresive manner without my wife saying slow down, yet again impressive.
These tires act like a performance tire, but feel more like a touring tire, you may or may not appreciate that feeling, and can be a little unsettling to the agresive driver who likes the connected to the road feeling normally associated with performance touring or sport tires.
Logevitity is yet to be seen, but Yokohama has a great reputation in that department.

So did I get everything I was looking for in new tires for my 2003 Acura TL type S?  I seriously doubt there was a better choice for me and my car, especially at this price.  Let them find the right tire for your needs at the right price.  Don't forget to check for rebates.<//text>

<rate>2< /rate>< Text>
I have been a customer of America's Tire Depot at the Shaw Ave location for over a year and a half, and have waited to write this review to see if things could improve. During my time as a customer, this store has gone through three managers and numerous employee changes in the shop. Though the personnel are nice and knoweledgable, there is still a huge disconnect and lack of organization in getting the work done. This has led to numerous appointments being made either online or by phone getting lost, or unacceptable wait times when they do remember your appointment. It took over 4hrs to get tires and an alignment with an appointment this last time, and sadly was not an isolated incident. So why do I go back?!... unfortunately, I am locked into a warranty battle. I originally purchased a set of four tires with a 45,000 mile warranty on 06-09-16. Almost a year later at only 4/32nds tread wear left  and 16,500 miles on the tires respectively, the tires were too worn for them to rotate any longer due to safety reasons, but not worn enough to warranty the tire. All rotations, alignments, and any other work suggested by ATD was done over that course of time. I continued to rotate the tires myself and bring the wear down to 2/32nds respectively and 22,000 miles. While they did eventually prorate the tires, increased fees on the same tire, labor, and the expired promotion that the original set were purchased under brought the 50% off proration total to nearly the same cost I originally paid on my first set. My advice, call around and compare estimates. While tire prices can be good here, by the time you add up warranty certificates, and shop labor, the cost of their tires overall may not be a great deal when compared to other companies that offer these services as part of the purchase. Also, with the lack of organization, long wait times, and hassle proving your warranty and infringing on your time as a customer, any cost savings, if any, are negligible.<//Text>
